@Ms. Billie M. Spaight
ACM was punning on the word "malaprop", used to describe a mistaken use of "fancy verbiage" by someone who doesn't understand what they're saying.
By analogy, ACM coined "malapop" for popping a word into a grid where it seems to fit, only to be forced to remove it when it turns up elsewhere and you have to admit it can't possibly belong where you had put it.

