@BobSolo
The English language generally works the other way round. You start with nouns, then develop other words from them. So here, SOT was first, then gave birth to beSOT. 
Be- is a productive prefix in English; i.e., you can add it to other transitive or reflexive verbs and produce something new but still recognizable. Its many offspring include beguile, bedazzle, beseech, and bestow. Feel free to try this at home, kids!

